                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G Commercial Agreement/57: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-26T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 26, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>484. Department’s circular telegram of September 23, 2 p.m. Cuban Secretary of
                    State verbally informs me that he has just telegraphed instructions to the Cuban
                    delegate at the League to support the endorsement of Resolution No. 81 if it
                    comes before the Assembly and is sending instructions to the Cuban Ambassador in
                    Washington to sign the Agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
